back pain is commonly regarded as the number one orthopedic complaint in the United Contemporary research shows more than % of people will develop low back pain at some point in their lifetime, often requiring formal medical While most patients understandably prefer a “quick fix,” numerous studies show that conservative care, most notably physical therapy, is the most effective Confounding the management of low back pain are the numerous diagnosis, treatment options and contradictory information associated with its The underlying goal of physical therapy, which is to increase mobility, while decreasing low back pain has repetitively provided consistent, positive Specifically diagnosed conditions, which are commonly treated in physical therapy are: Degenerative Disc Disease, Degenerative Joint Disease, Arthritis, Herniated Bulging Disc, Stenosis, Sciatica, SI Joint Dysfunction, Radiculopathy and TREATMENTS Treatment of low back pain, whether acute or chronic, typically begins with decreasing inflammations and This includes reducing muscular tension of the lumbar Restoring range of motion and functional mobility are also key components of rehab at this With a reduction of painful symptoms, patients are usually able to gradually return to their normal daily ​ Following a reduction of inflammation, more advanced techniques are then These treatments aim to reduce spinal compression, promote proper vertebral joint function and reduce radicular Spinal manipulation mobilization, postural education and core stability allow for a patient’s return to full MANUAL THERAPY Manual therapy, including soft tissue manipulation, joint mobilization and dry needling, are commonly used to decrease pain and muscular Skilled physical therapy intervention can undoubtedly increase blood flow to these areas and ultimately reduce Contemporary research consistently concludes positive results with the physical contact between a therapist and THERAPEUTIC EXERCISE PROGRAMS Therapeutic exercise programs, including both stretching and strengthening are the hallmarks of productive physical The application of proper posture training and restoring normal movements patterns are necessary for early resumption of Specific stability exercises are utilized to improve neck and upper quarter control, while also reducing the possibility of Contact Us Message Fixed Annuity? A fixed annuity is essentially a Certificate of Deposit (CD) sold by an insurance company instead of a Fixed annuities pay a guaranteed rate of return for a specified period of time (usually years). In addition to providing a guaranteed rate of return for the investment term, fixed annuities, and all annuities, give you the opportunity to turn those savings into lifelong The fixed annuity guarantee is backed by the financial strength of the issuing insurance IMPORTANT NOTE : You have likely heard of a fixed annuity referred to as any of these other names: CD type annuity Multi Year Guaranteed Annuity (MYGA) Single Premium Deferred Annuity (SPDA) Traditional Fixed Annuity Flexible Premium Deferred Annuity (FPDA) Fixed Annuity Definition: With a fixed annuity, the insurance company guarantees both the rate of return (the interest rate) and the payout to the Although the word “fixed” might suggest otherwise, the interest rate on a fixed annuity can change over The contract will explain whether, how and when this can Often the interest rate is fixed for a number of years and then changes periodically based on current Payouts can be for an entire lifetime, or you can choose another time Source: “Learn to Invest, Investment Types, Annuities, Fixed ” Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA). How Systems Shift — Collective Change Lab 0 Skip to Content About People Our story What we believe Our Work How systems shift Questions we re exploring How we partner for change Resources Blog Systems change stories Publications Our engagements Credits CONTACT Open Menu Close Menu About People Our story What we believe Our Work How systems shift Questions we re exploring How we partner for change Resources Blog Systems change stories Publications Our engagements Credits CONTACT Open Menu Close Menu Folder: About Back People Our story What we believe Folder: Our Work Back Current Page: How systems shift Questions we re exploring How we partner for change Folder: Resources Back Blog Systems change stories Publications Our engagements Credits CONTACT How systems shift Transforming our systems to be more just and equitable for all will require new ways of working It demands practices that cultivate collective wisdom and give rise to evolved levels of thinking and action addressing systemic At a systems level, transformation involves a radical shift in system culture (mindsets, relationships, power) and system structure (policies, practices, resource flows). To create more radical outcomes we need radical containers (intentional ways of working together that transform connection, learning and collective potential). Being more “radical” doesn’t require inventing something Practices—most from cultures—such as peacemaking circles, truth and reconciliation, spiritual rituals and other restorative justice approaches can help guide These practices, which come from many different cultures, tend to have five qualities in common that support the work of transformational read our Theory of change For more, read John Kania’s blog, “Empathy, Integration, Letting Go & ” ﻿ Six Conditions of Systems Change Employing radical containers—not on the periphery but as integral to our mainstream problem solving efforts—will begin to transform systems for We won’t achieve our collective potential without The framework presented here helps explain The inverted triangle depicts six conditions of systems change that hold social and environmental problems in These exist at three different levels of visibility: structural, relational, and The largest barriers to change, and also the greatest opportunities for transformation, are the deeper conditions of systems change: relationships and connections, power dynamics, and mental Ways of working together that share the qualities of radical containers are essential to shifting these deeper Amplifying the voices and wisdom of people from around the world who are effectively cultivating radical containers is core work of the Collective Change Collective Feedback? powered by Olark live chat software Skip to content Demos Capabilities Menu Toggle Virtual Events Hybrid Events portfolio Resources Menu Toggle Blog Case Studies Press Releases Glossary Job Descriptions templates Who We Are Contact Main Menu Demos Capabilities Menu Toggle Virtual Events Hybrid Events portfolio Resources Menu Toggle Blog Case Studies Press Releases Glossary Job Descriptions templates Who We Are Contact Virtual Events In the world was forced to make big In the events industry, virtually all events were canceled—except for the ones that were able to quickly pivot to a virtual or hybrid In , live events began to return, but the industry has changed Live is no longer the only option, and the advantages of the virtual format mean they continue to be the preferred option for many events—and will continue to A virtual event is a version of a live event where all the action happens Instead of attendees showing up to a convention center or hotel, they log into a website or event platform from wherever they And instead of walking around an exhibition hall, watching a keynote speech, or sitting in a theater to attend a panel discussion, attendees do these things in virtual For just about every element of a live event, there’s an online counterpart that is just as Events can be % virtual, with all elements online, or they can include both live elements and virtual In this case, they’re called hybrid events, since they’re a mix of both Why go virtual for your next event? Virtual events are a viable, valuable alternative to events for so many Here are a few: Expand your attendee base – People aren’t restricted by geography or cost because they don’t have to travel or book accommodations to attend the You could expand your audience to the next state over, the opposite coast, or even other countries just by going The online environment is ideal for monetization – From event websites to apps to virtual event environments, there are plenty of opportunities for event brands and sponsors to expose an audience to their marketing immersive events have staying power – The content created for a virtual event can be made available afterwards, extending the life and the ROI of your It can also be repackaged and repurposed for other marketing Virtual Events Offer Incredible Analytics One of the most important and valuable differences between virtual events and live events is something that may not be immediately obvious: The simple fact is, because a virtual event takes place online, it has the power to generate a huge amount of useful It’s infinitely easier to track attendees online than it is to track them at a live Once an individual logs into your event website, you have access to everything they do at the event, including what site pages or content they visit and how long they spend Plus, you can easily track individuals and just as easily aggregate data for statistical It’s very easy to gather such invaluable Your attendees do a lot of the work for you, just by filling in registration forms and And since each attendee has their own unique login identifier, you have the ability to match demographic information to attendee behavior data, giving you even more information about what specific groups and individuals do at the For instance: Virtual event data can tell you how many people watch a presentation and how many stop watching before the It can also tell you the exact moment they turn the presentation off and even what event content they choose to watch after Matching user data with demographic data can show you how different groups of people interact with your For instance, it can indicate which event content is most popular with managers, or what brands and products are of most interest to Tracking engagement data via rates and other interaction indicators can record levels of engagement for speakers and other presentations, as well as sponsorship and exhibitor and surveys add extra layers, as you can use email matching to correlate event activity and survey Are attendees with higher engagement levels more likely to be satisfied with their event experience? This strategy gives you the chance to find In short, virtual events allow you to track attendee behavior and attitudes at a huge array of event This gives you enormous potential for using data to create better events and improve both your event ROI and your relationship with your event An Immersive Virtual Event Is Not a Webinar Webinars have been around since the , and they’re considered by some to be the first virtual But these days, the technology that powers virtual events has moved far beyond the kind of tech that’s used for A webinar is a seminar that’s typically produced to disseminate information or provide education on a They may include elements such as a Q&A session or panel discussion, or video displays, and live And they’re often held on platforms like Zoom or Google A virtu

Benefits of Using POS Systems for Merchants and Customers As more consumers solely use credit cards for their purchases, it has never been more important for organizations to utilize credit card processing As today s marketplaces become more digitized, it has become vital for businesses to adapt to new and emerging This is especially true when it comes to diversifying the method of accepted According to a survey of 1,800 consumers, % of respondents said that it is important for a business to offer the ability to pay with a credit Expectations were even higher for certain types of businesses, such as restaurants, supermarkets, and retail In other words, it s important for any business today, regardless of size, to readily accept credit card payments, whether it is on a point of sale (POS) device, online, or over the However, doing so requires having a provider that can handle each credit card transaction safely and securely through credit card How Credit Card Processing Works The act of making a purchase using a credit card triggers a complex process where data is sent from the customer s credit card to the merchant s POS device, and then to the cardholder s bank - all in the span of a few In fact, swiping or tapping a credit or debit card and signing the receipt are just the first and final steps of credit card A comprehensive breakdown of this process can be summarized in 3 Payment Authorization The first stage of any credit card transaction is In the store, the customer pays by either swiping (magnetic stripe), tapping (contactless card), or dipping (EMV chip cards) their They can also use a digital wallet linked to their credit card, like Apple Online, the customer inputs their credit card details into a payment form on an app or For phone transactions, a virtual terminal provides secure credit card The merchant s credit card terminal or website sends the cardholder s details, including the credit card number, expiration date, security code, and payment amount to the store s acquiring bank or This information is forwarded to the appropriate credit card network (e.g. Visa, Mastercard), which then passes it on to the customer s issuing bank for Payment Authentication The issuing bank receives the payment request and verifies whether the cardholder has the available balance to make the The bank will also conduct security measures to authenticate the cardholder s details and determine whether the transaction shows any signs of fraudulent If everything is confirmed to be genuine, the bank account approves the transaction and communicates this to the payment processor and then to the credit card reader or Clearing The clearing stage is when details of the transaction are sent to the cardholder and merchant services in the form of At the end of every business day, the merchant sends a batch of approved credit and debit card transactions to the acquiring bank or The card processing company then forwards details of each transaction to the corresponding credit card network, which then forwards it to the appropriate Funds and shares of transaction fees are moved between banks, credit card networks, and acquiring processors to keep the system Parties Involved in the Cred

Vaccine Whole Inactivated Virus vaccine (wiV) Coronovirus Home Vaccine Corporate Team About Blog News White Paper Why Whole inactivated virus vaccine? ​ Tried and tested technology platform that cannot cause the disease ​Inactivated vaccines are made from microorganisms that have been killed through physical or chemical These killed organisms cannot cause the Multiple vaccines of this type are approved and available in the market (e.g. Polio, Hepatitis A, Rabies, ) WIV can be used in vulnerable populations (i.e., pregnant women, older and certain immunocompromised patients). ​ WIV vaccines have already been produced and tested at scale in China, where millions of vaccinations have been Sinovac and Sinopharm s vaccines have been given Emergency Use Approval by the A solution to virus mutations ​ WIV vaccines are more likely to remain effective and relevant even if antigens of the genome mutate in contrast to single or based vaccines, such as mRNA and or Adenovirus ​ Is a Whole Virion based vaccine ​WIV vaccines contain the Nucleocapsid N protein as well as the Spike, providing broader protection than vaccines based only on the Spike protein, and may provide protection against other ​ Stable and compatible with current distribution infrastructure ​ WIV vaccines are known to be more stable than live attenuated viral (LAV) vaccines and have storage compatible (fully-liquid stable in degree Celsius) with existing supply chains to ensure ​ A Vaccine of Choice: Reliable platform Better able to deal with viral mutations Meets WHO Target Product Profile Ease of administration Compatible with existing supply chains (2-to-8-degree Celsius) Protection without infection Outbreak response Antigen sparing adjuvant Highly scalable manufacturing process Industry Updates Check out Industry Updates for our analysis on how Vaccinations are progressing around the World Read More Industry Update Volume Safe, effective, low cost vaccine for all : How do inactivated vaccines work? A leased line is a dedicated internet connection that is leased exclusively by you, or your With a Leased Line connection, you will benefit from % of the bandwidth because your internet connection isn’t shared with anyone Is a reliable connection important? An unstable internet connection will have a negative impact on your organisations productivity and So if you rely on a stable and resilient internet connection for Business Continuity, then a Leased Line is the perfect Leased Lines provide uncontended bandwidth for your premises, to provide unmatched reliability and Uncontented bandwidth is a term used to describe a fixed internet connection speed that isn’t affected by peak usage Leased Lines can also be synchronous, giving you the same upload and download speeds and are ideal for those companies which require higher a capacity internet Fast, reliable and secure ethernet connectivity that exceeds expectations with a dedicated leased line between your business and a local One of the fundamental and most important differences between a leased line internet connection and a broadband internet connection from a business perspective is that leased lines come with Service Level Agreements as standard and broadband connections do A Service Level Agreement is a minimum standard that you can expect from your provider, that also outlines what action the provider will take should the internet connection fail or fall short of those Cost can be a factor Leased lines are typically more expensive than a broadband internet However, you’re not comparing products and therefore, whilst it’s only natural to compare the cost of two products, it’s more beneficial to consider the differences in value between broadband and leased line Whilst your costs will increase if you move from a broadband connection to a leased line connection, you be paying for additional features and benefits So is it the best option for your business? Whilst there is no hard and fast rule when it comes to a business, we’d almost always recommend a leased line internet connection over Whilst this costs more, we believe that the benefits of leased lines far outweigh the A dedicated leased line means you will have a robust internet connection that you and your business can rely upon and with the internet being critical to the productivity of most businesses, we think this is crucial for any successful Want to know more? The coverage for your vehicle must meet state It consists of collision and comprehensive You might also add roadside assistance and personal injury protection (PIP) coverage as well as uninsured underinsured motorist Collision insurance pays out when your vehicle gets involved in a collision of any It could be a collision with another vehicle, a mailbox, a fence, the garage door, Comprehensive insurance pays out when your vehicle incurs damage from a named peril such as a tornado, hurricane, fire, hail, It also covers The PIP policy component provides you medical coverage whether you get involved in a accident or the person at fault for the accident has no The PIP coverage pays your medical bills and for some types of rehabilitative Some policies also cover transportation to and from medical Uninsured motorist coverage protects your vehicle when the person at fault for the accident has no insurance or too little insurance to cover the accident This policy ensures you can repair your car or Roadside assistance covers your need for a tow truck, fuel if you run out of gas while on the road, emergency tire change, Contact Affinity Insurance Partners serving Pittsburgh, PA, today to obtain the full coverage policy you We’re here to Posted in Auto Insurance Tagged Affinity Insurance Partners , Pittsburgh PA How commercial insurance protects your small business Posted

Discovery Proteomics Efficacy Models Press Portal Contact Us General Info Terms Privacy Proteomics Proteomics is the study of the proteome, which consists of all the proteins produced in an organism, cell, or biological Using high resolution mass spectrometry, data from the proteome can provide insight into proteins and their signaling pathways as the drivers of human physiology and Yatiri Bio explicitly prioritizes this data as the key to understanding how and why particular drugs successfully eradicate Recent advances in this technology allow for the identification and quantification of thousands ( 8,000) of proteins per In addition, the signaling pathways can be accurately monitored via analysis of post translational modifications (PTM) that steer biochemical Consequently, these analyses address the relevant disease on a cellular level including direct observation of the effects of drug The advantage of studying the proteome (versus the current standard of identifying only a selective few biomarkers) is that we are able to identify more robust biomarker signatures, improve patient selection, and drive therapies for personalized Proteomics (bottom-up review) Mass Spectrometry (Isobaric labeling) Bioinformatics Yatiri Bio develops proprietary computational tools (differential expression, pathway enrichment, sample outliers and other analyses) that employ machine learning techniques such as unsupervised clustering and methods to specifically explore proteomics data in the context of human We move beyond the statistical modeling by employing our vast experience and deep understanding of experimental design with the goal of utilizing all elements of the captured data and converting it to actionable The result of this work is a fully interactive data portal ProteoBrowser TM and ProteoPathway TM tailored for each experiment, and optimized with collaborative Cancer Molecular subtypes Proteogenomics of CRC Models Yatiri Bio has developed a portfolio of cellular models backed by clinical proteome data that are tailored to match molecularly defined cancer Our ProteoModels TM can be used for optimized patient selection, rational exploration of combinational therapies, drug repurposing, identifying resistance mechanisms, and drug discovery with robust and translatable biomarkers from the While most compounds show robust activity in cellular and animal models, % of the compounds that progress to clinical trials fail due to poor correlation between the models and the patients they are meant to The incorporation of accurate efficacy models will streamline the entire drug discovery process, guide early research choices, and make it easier and far less costly to match the right therapeutic with the right Clinical Cosecha del Sur was born on a single afternoon visit to a Colombian farm, after having the most amazing cup of coffee of my Since then, my goal has been to pay tribute to the hands and cultures that craft this amazing In March of , I was on a farm in Valle del Cauca, Colombia, developing a project in the hemp industry where I was served a cup of One cup turned into three, and the conversation slowly evolved from discussing hemp cultivation to the hectares of coffee trees located on the other side of the While speaking with my friend and owner of the farm, Liliana Gutiérrez Gaviria, I was moved by her passion and desire to create a thriving farming She had gone “all-in” and had sacrificed so much to pursue her dream of owning her own farm and employing local women to work for She explained that it is extremely difficult to make a profit because the market prices for coffee were well below the cost of In order to grow coffee that is of the utmost quality, environmentally friendly, and beneficial to the surrounding rural community, it would require significant capital Furthermore, because this coffee had not been commercially sold for years, this truly was a unique cup of coffee that could not be bought in any store in the At that moment, the dots were I proposed to Lilliana to give me a few months to figure out how to create a coffee brand, export, import, roast, and This resulted in a partnership predicated on friendship, trust, and a simple By leveraging my international commodity trading experience to manage some of the challenging aspects of the coffee industry including logistics, financial risk, and market risk, I was able to find ways to pass the savings back to the I also promised that I would tell the world her story to inspire others like I was that In May of , I decided to take the leap and start Cosecha del Sur Coffee Company (Spanish for “southern harvest”). My mission is to inspire others through radical transparency, allowing you, the customer, to feel a direct connection to the amazing origins of our I hope that we can take this journey together, using coffee as our guide to explore the + countries that produce this incredible drink that plays such a significant role in our daily Charlie Stephens Founder, Cosecha del Sur Coffee Sign up for updates Promotions, new products and Directly to your Subscribe Instagram Copyright © , Cosecha del Sur Coffee Close Cart Shopping Cart Your cart is currently Enable cookies to use the shopping cart t: e (- ) Remove Item Quantity Discount: - Subtotal $0.00 Taxes and shipping calculated at checkout Checkout Choosing a selection results in a full page Press the space key then arrow keys to make a   Account – Cosecha del Sur Coffee Skip to content Free shipping for orders over $40! (Mark 8:36) Spoiler alert: ​ This bible verse has endured over the centuries as a reminder that we can’t put our price tag on what matters ​ Yet, time and again, businesses have put profits above all — leading our world to the brink of a climate catastrophe, an inequality crisis, and the greatest extinction of other creatures since the ​ Can we align growing returns with the greater good? Former investment banker turned business ethicist Dawn Carpenter believes we can — and that figuring out how will shape the ​ In What Does It Profit? Dawn talks with the world’s leading thinkers, researchers, entrepreneurs and executives, exploring the most innovative ways we can reconcile capitalism’s demand for profit with the long term of people and the ​ From investing to conscious consumerism to business ethics in this age of extremes, Dawn is your guide to the ideas and experiments driving the business What Does It Profit? Can conscious capitalism save the world? After finding herself sharing an elevator ride with JPMorgan CEO Jamie Dimon, she was struck by a sobering question– what was she doing with her life? She loved being a banker and derived great satisfaction in bringing together those who needed capital with those who had excess to But was this all she was called to do? Her answer was an energetic “not even ” ​ Motivated by a higher purpose, Dawn set out to find the answer to the challenging questions of why do we work and what responsibility do we have for the wealth that is generated by that work?
